      <!-- ── The logic graph ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <section>
        <div class="sec-kicker">The unit of audit</div>
        <h2>Every result is a graph of statements</h2>
        <p>
          A result is stored as a <strong>logic graph</strong>: nodes are statements — a setup, a
          definition, an assumption, a lemma, the headline theorem — and edges record
          dependencies. This turns the global question "is this proved and faithful?" into a
          per-node one, so a change re-opens only the nodes it touches instead of the whole paper.
        </p>

        <div class="figure">
          <svg class="svg-fig" viewBox="0 0 480 290" role="img"
               aria-label="A schematic logic graph: setup, definition, and cited nodes at the bottom; an assumption and two lemmas in the middle; the headline theorem at the top. Node color encodes review status and a green underlay marks the critical path.">
